2) Writer a code to reverse a C-Style string (C-String means that “abcd” is represented as 5 characters including the null character.)

//A: strlen(“abcd”) = 5
Approach1:- exchange the first and the last letter of the string
for(int i = 0; i < strlen(str)/2;  i++)
{
	char temp;
	temp = str[i];
	str[i] = str[strlen(str)-1-1-i];
	str[strlen(str)-1-1-i] = temp;
}

